reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lots of things to screw together, but a pretty solid build once done.
reviews.reviewText: This thing arrived in a pretty flat box, so i knew at that point that there would be a bit of work to get it to look like the picture on Amazon. Generally, this type of furniture is mostly a small number of particle board pieces stuck together with a small number of one-size-fits-all screws. This table is actually more plastic than particle board, and this lends it a greater stability. The engineering and overall end product is quite a bit better than an IKEA product of similar size and price. It was a little more work (50% more screws/fasteners) to get it together, but shouldn't furniture take some effort to assemble? I like this thing.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Hard to assemble, poor quality
reviews.reviewText: The holes for screws during assemby were not in the nightstand so we could not properly assemble the nightstand. It also has screw holes that show on the top of the night stand that gives it a very cheap appearance. It has excessive parts and the assembling it is a nightmare. It is poor quality and I do not recommend.

reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for a minimalist, not me 🤣
reviews.reviewText: This is probably one of a handful of purchases on Amazon that I regret...allow me to explain 🤣 As soon as I saw the package on my porch, I knew this was small based on how small the box was 😒. Assembly was a pain {comes with tools} there are so many pieces for such a small stand. It's sturdy. If you buy the white one, the screws are going to show {unless you touch them up with a white polish/paint}●1st pic: next to my king size bed this Itty bitty thing looks like an accent piece not a nightstand●2nd pic: the binder was too wide to fit between the legs {to show the actual width}If you're looking for a bigger nightstand, keep looking. I'll re-purpose this after I order a bigger nightstand.
